257
00:12:06,492 --> 00:12:12,298
Hiromi GO! After just one sip of each, he chooses A.

258
00:12:12,752 --> 00:12:13,907
Let’s wait.

259
00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:20,035
Now he waits for the results, watching the others on the monitor.

260
00:12:21,307 --> 00:12:26,413
But Tendo-san has tons of them at home, right? Her cellar’s packed with wine.

261
00:12:26,438 --> 00:12:30,883
Ouch, going up against Professor Tendo...

262
00:12:30,908 --> 00:12:34,275
Next up, this guest.

263
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:37,362
Here we have Ms. Tendo.

264
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:39,975
Yoshimi Tendo.

265
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:44,090
With a one-of-a-kind voice that combines power and delicacy,

266
00:12:44,115 --> 00:12:47,702
she’s a top star who continues to lead the enka world.

267
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,511
Do you drink wine often?

268
00:12:50,536 --> 00:12:53,914
We’ll get together and have some now and then,

269
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:57,543
but I don’t really down it in big gulps.

270
00:12:57,568 --> 00:12:59,989
I just sip a little at a time.

271
00:13:00,014 --> 00:13:02,014
That’s how you’re supposed to do it.

272
00:13:03,173 --> 00:13:05,740
You’re meant to savor it, hold it in your mouth.

273
00:13:05,765 --> 00:13:08,360
People who chug it are dangerous.

274
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:14,295
Tendo, who has a huge wine cellar at home, starts with wine A.

275
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,344
She checks the color,

276
00:13:20,839 --> 00:13:23,555
gently lets a sip flow into her mouth,

277
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:27,222
and slowly rolls it around on her tongue.

278
00:13:28,179 --> 00:13:30,882
She nods, looking confident.

279
00:13:31,443 --> 00:13:34,413
Oh...she looks confident.

280
00:13:36,448 --> 00:13:39,907
Tendo even seems relaxed, totally at ease.

281
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:45,205
With a sharp gaze, she checks the color,

282
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:52,178
then gently lets this one flow into her mouth as well.

283
00:13:55,652 --> 00:13:59,320
She's smiles with satisfaction

284
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,309
She knows

285
00:14:05,544 --> 00:14:07,558
Her answer is...

286
00:14:09,793 --> 00:14:11,793
Split answer!

287
00:14:18,891 --> 00:14:21,044
When I first sip...

288
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:25,798
There’s this soft, really lovely aroma that spreads out.

289
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,902
I’m confident about this.

290
00:14:31,459 --> 00:14:33,539
That’s the opinion of someone who actually drinks.

291
00:14:33,564 --> 00:14:36,909
Right off the bat, they’re split.

292
00:14:36,934 --> 00:14:40,095
The utterly confident Yoshimi Tendo

293
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:43,474
heads to room B, opposite from GO.

294
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:48,643
What should I do?

295
00:14:52,358 --> 00:14:57,389
Why is Hiromi-san sitting there all hunched up and tiny like that?

296
00:14:57,414 --> 00:14:58,964
He picked the most awkward spot to sit.

297
00:14:58,994 --> 00:15:00,633
Bad perspective?

298
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:07,350
Next up is...

299
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:13,851
Ryoma Takeuchi

300
00:15:13,876 --> 00:15:21,654
a top actor in constant demand for dramas and films, known for his strong presence and wide range of roles.

301
00:15:21,679 --> 00:15:23,447
So, how about wine? Do you usually drink it?

302
00:15:23,472 --> 00:15:24,725
I drink a little wine, yes.

303
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:27,393
But something in the one-million-yen range, I’ve never...

304
00:15:27,418 --> 00:15:29,136
Right, yeah, of course, of course.

305
00:15:29,161 --> 00:15:30,800
There should be an overwhelming difference between them.

306
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:31,430
Of course.

307
00:15:31,455 --> 00:15:33,995
I've got all my senses on high alert,

308
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,386
so I feel like I can pull this off.

309
00:15:35,411 --> 00:15:39,315
Will those hypersensitive antennas pick up the right answer?

310
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:42,582
First up is wine A, chosen by Go.

311
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,315
He's used to this.

312
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,165
It really suits him.

313
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:47,012
Yeah, he's clearly done this a lot.

314
00:15:47,077 --> 00:15:50,658
He must have practiced somewhere.

315
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:52,960
He takes two sips of the wine he's been served.

316
00:15:52,985 --> 00:15:55,773
He swirls it, then goes in for the aroma.

317
00:15:56,920 --> 00:16:00,195
Oh, he's gone for a third sip.

318
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:00,892
Huh?

319
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:04,155
Takeuchi just keeps drinking.

320
00:16:04,179 --> 00:16:05,495
Go on, just finish the whole thing.

321
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,498
He actually drank it all.

322
00:16:06,523 --> 00:16:09,134
Is he gonna be okay after this?

323
00:16:09,159 --> 00:16:12,580
Next is wine B, chosen by Tendo.

324
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:16,657
First, he checks the smell.

325
00:16:17,540 --> 00:16:18,324
Hmm?

326
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:21,846
Did those sharp senses pick up something?

327
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,821
He quickly checks the taste as well.

328
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:30,908
He's a real drinker.

329
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:32,700
Okay, here we go.

330
00:16:32,725 --> 00:16:34,140
Just a small sip of this one.

331
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,086
And the answer he gives is...

332
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:39,723
Oh!

333
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:54,113
It felt like it had softened over, say, eighty years or so,

334
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:57,491
like it had really aged and matured.

335
00:16:57,516 --> 00:17:01,115
There was this slight fallen-leaves kind of nuance too.

336
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:02,763
Listen to this guy.

337
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:06,886
He's just as confident.

338
00:17:07,069 --> 00:17:09,489
So which one of them is actually right?

339
00:17:23,776 --> 00:17:25,481
Next up...

340
00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:30,755
Atsushi Tamura.

341
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:32,785
Not only does he host variety shows,

342
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:34,615
he also appears on news and educational programs,

343
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:38,465
a top-tier entertainer with a truly broad range.

344
00:17:38,490 --> 00:17:40,300
I really, really wanted to do the wine segment.

345
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,326
Seriously?

346
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:44,702
I'm a wine lover, I actually go to places like Napa Valley,

347
00:17:44,727 --> 00:17:45,883
and do all kinds of tours

348
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:47,928
Annoying, right?

349
00:17:47,953 --> 00:17:50,848
I can't help it, I just really love wine.

350
00:17:50,873 --> 00:17:51,870
Very reassuring.

351
00:17:51,895 --> 00:17:57,731
He loves wine so much he even visits the world's most famous wine regions.

352
00:18:00,406 --> 00:18:03,464
With practiced hands, he checks the bouquet.

353
00:18:06,644 --> 00:18:09,977
then smoothly lets it roll over his tongue.

354
00:18:17,662 --> 00:18:19,095
He looks experienced

355
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:27,614
Next, wine B, which only Tendo chose.

356
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:31,103
He carefully checks the color first.

357
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,292
He's really studying the color.

358
00:18:34,318 --> 00:18:35,824
Even though those glasses are tinted...

359
00:18:35,848 --> 00:18:37,549
Then take the glasses off!

360
00:18:39,322 --> 00:18:40,886
What's the point otherwise?

361
00:18:41,434 --> 00:18:42,300
True.

362
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:46,275
You can't see anything with those still on.

363
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:48,360
With just a single sip of this one,

364
00:18:49,442 --> 00:18:51,230
he goes, 'Wow, that's good.'

365
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:53,415
Same as before.

366
00:18:53,438 --> 00:18:56,110
Can he really tell?

367
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,572
And his answer is...?

368
00:19:03,029 --> 00:19:05,033
I'm relieved

369
00:19:07,112 --> 00:19:08,764
Knew it.

370
00:19:08,789 --> 00:19:10,065
I was sure it'd be that.

371
00:19:10,324 --> 00:19:12,324
(Could be bad)

372
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:16,776
When you let it sit in your mouth,

373
00:19:16,803 --> 00:19:18,475
there's this kind of weight to it,

374
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:21,193
and even an aroma that feels like it carries history.

375
00:19:21,218 --> 00:19:23,803
I knew right away it was A.

376
00:19:24,363 --> 00:19:27,866
The way he phrases it is so annoyingly good.

377
00:19:28,683 --> 00:19:31,069
He does sound pretty convincing though.

378
00:19:31,094 --> 00:19:33,695
We still don't know yet.

379
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:38,377
Still, having Atsushi here is reassuring.

380
00:19:38,402 --> 00:19:42,214
That white ventriloquist dummy Takeuchi brought is kinda creepy, you know?

381
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:46,600
(ventriloquist)         (dummy)

382
00:19:46,626 --> 00:19:48,921
He's wearing white...

383
00:19:48,946 --> 00:19:51,957
It's because of the perspective

384
00:19:55,460 --> 00:20:01,933
Self-proclaimed wine lover Atsushi heads to Room A, where the white ventriloquist dummy awaits.

385
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,265
I knew it.

386
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:13,715
So Tendo went over there.

387
00:20:13,740 --> 00:20:14,912
Yeah, that's right.

388
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:16,705
That's the thing.

389
00:20:17,282 --> 00:20:19,515
But sometimes one person ends up the sole winner.

390
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:20,583
That's pretty cool when it happens.

391
00:20:20,608 --> 00:20:24,131
There have been a few times where someone wins the wine round all by themselves.

392
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:27,755
And a new challenger appears already.

393
00:20:27,780 --> 00:20:29,340
Now, GACKT-sama.

394
00:20:29,364 --> 00:20:31,763
Yes, it is GACKT-sama.

395
00:20:31,788 --> 00:20:35,467
Top-tier entertainer GACKT-sama.

396
00:20:35,492 --> 00:20:40,675
This time he's taking on the challenge completely alone, with no time rest between questions.

397
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:46,311
How far will he extend his personal streak of 81 consecutive wins?

398
00:20:46,336 --> 00:20:50,649
No one's going to miss something this easy.

399
00:20:51,424 --> 00:20:54,519
That's what he's saying people!

400
00:20:55,114 --> 00:20:57,122
I haven't given my answer yet, though.

401
00:20:57,147 --> 00:21:02,908
The absolute champion, GACKT-sama, starts with wine A.

402
00:21:03,829 --> 00:21:05,765
Wait, the glass is different?

403
00:21:05,790 --> 00:21:07,115
From ours? For real?

404
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,315
Looks like it.

405
00:21:09,118 --> 00:21:10,311
The glass is different

406
00:21:10,868 --> 00:21:14,694
Please focus on GACKT's wine glass.

407
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,135
That's his own glass, right?

408
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:18,043
Yes, we have him bring it every year.

409
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:19,633
Because it's his personal glass.

410
00:21:19,658 --> 00:21:22,557
It's his Dragon Glass.

411
00:21:23,181 --> 00:21:27,653
He gently swirls his special glass and carefully checks the aroma.

412
00:21:28,381 --> 00:21:32,859
Then slowly, he sips with his elevated palate...

413
00:21:35,313 --> 00:21:36,382
Chu

414
00:21:36,407 --> 00:21:37,542
Chu chu

415
00:21:37,563 --> 00:21:38,944
Chu chu chu

416
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:42,702
...delicately tasting every nuance.

417
00:21:44,187 --> 00:21:46,038
Right.

418
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:55,255
Now all eyes are on Wine B.

419
00:21:55,280 --> 00:22:00,416
He gives this one a faint swirl as well and checks the bouquet.

420
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:06,224
Do you really have to lift it up that high?

421
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,894
To see it in the light or something?

422
00:22:08,919 --> 00:22:11,930
Then, quite casually, he takes a sip.

423
00:22:18,780 --> 00:22:22,154
GACKT's verdict is...

424
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,330
Okay.

425
00:22:26,445 --> 00:22:28,814
Which one did he pick?

426
00:22:31,463 --> 00:22:32,465
B was fast.

427
00:22:32,490 --> 00:22:34,406
Just from one sip.

428
00:22:37,756 --> 00:22:38,930
This year as well...

429
00:22:38,955 --> 00:22:44,631
To keep other teams from relaxing as soon as GACKT picks his answer,

430
00:22:44,643 --> 00:22:48,533
we've prepared a special room.

431
00:22:48,558 --> 00:22:53,393
We won't say which one GACKT chose yet

432
00:22:53,405 --> 00:22:57,167
We'll only explain why he chose his answer.

433
00:22:57,480 --> 00:23:02,514
Did he already know about this rare wine?

434
00:23:02,539 --> 00:23:09,240
There are a few vintages in history that are called so-called "godly years."

435
00:23:09,260 --> 00:23:16,328
And this '47 is said to be a truly miraculous year.

436
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:19,197
But...

437
00:23:19,222 --> 00:23:21,558
Because of the extreme heat,

438
00:23:21,570 --> 00:23:23,667
the acidity

439
00:23:23,679 --> 00:23:25,251
has

440
00:23:25,263 --> 00:23:27,706
basically disappeared.

441
00:23:27,731 --> 00:23:29,540
The acidity disappeared?

442
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:31,647
For a wine that's been aged this long,

443
00:23:31,671 --> 00:23:33,320
of course the quality is high,

444
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:38,560
but compared to other La Missions, it doesn't quite reach that level.

445
00:23:38,662 --> 00:23:41,887
He's insanely knowledgeable.

446
00:23:41,912 --> 00:23:44,576
On the other bottle,

447
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:47,998
the clusters are

448
00:23:48,010 --> 00:23:51,085
rougher compared to La Mission.

449
00:23:51,110 --> 00:23:56,602
You can tell which one is La Mission...

450
00:23:56,614 --> 00:23:58,236
just by looking at it.

451
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:00,063
No way!

452
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:01,971
That's amazing.

453
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,074
He's unbelievable.

454
00:24:03,099 --> 00:24:06,540
How was that, hearing GACKT's explanation just now?

455
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:10,155
He talked about the heatwave continuing and all that,

456
00:24:10,180 --> 00:24:11,683
so I feel a bit more confident in my own choice.

457
00:24:11,857 --> 00:24:14,973
Seriously?

458
00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:20,123
GACKT, currently on a personal streak of 81 straight wins.

459
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:25,063
Which wine did he choose, A or B?

460
00:24:25,585 --> 00:24:29,385
(nuts counter)

461
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:32,857
Next up...

462
00:24:33,184 --> 00:24:35,059
Here they come.

463
00:24:35,260 --> 00:24:36,475
Do your best!

464
00:24:36,499 --> 00:24:38,476
Kei Inoo

465
00:24:38,488 --> 00:24:45,134
not only an idol in Hey! Say! JUMP but also drawing attention for his acting.

466
00:24:45,439 --> 00:24:47,104
Mitsuomi Takahashi

467
00:24:47,129 --> 00:24:53,525
A top actor who plays a wide range of roles and leaves a strong impression in many works.

468
00:24:53,549 --> 00:24:54,914
How are you with wine?

469
00:24:54,940 --> 00:25:01,255
I don't drink that much wine, but last year in France I had some vintage wines...

470
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:06,175
including a bottle from the year Hey! Say! JUMP debuted, which I got to try.

471
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:09,059
So if we're talking in that general direction, I think I can probably guess it.

472
00:25:09,084 --> 00:25:10,030
You might nail this.

473
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:11,315
And Mitsu-san, how about you?

474
00:25:11,340 --> 00:25:15,275
Well, in the drama '50-Minute Lover,'

475
00:25:15,299 --> 00:25:18,278
there are scenes where I drink wine,

476
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:22,529
so in that sense I've done some studying as well,

477
00:25:22,554 --> 00:25:24,130
I've got this.

478
00:25:24,155 --> 00:25:26,191
Thank you for that very ordinary comment.

479
00:25:29,928 --> 00:25:34,699
You were talking like you were about to say something amazing, you know.

480
00:25:34,724 --> 00:25:40,995
First, let's start with Wine A, which everyone except Tendo chose.

481
00:25:42,075 --> 00:25:44,075
(gulp)

482
00:25:44,090 --> 00:25:45,610
He's drinking a lot.

483
00:25:45,635 --> 00:25:48,021
Is he ok?

484
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:51,220
Whoa, whoa, you don't have to finish the whole thing.

485
00:25:51,562 --> 00:25:57,953
The lead of the new drama is the playful type who just gulps it all down.

486
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:05,797
He really is drinking the whole thing.

487
00:26:08,199 --> 00:26:10,632
And the answer they gave is...

488
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,257
Ready, set...

489
00:26:13,584 --> 00:26:14,709
Oh!

490
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,210
They all matched!

491
00:26:19,235 --> 00:26:20,710
Whoa.

492
00:26:21,727 --> 00:26:28,653
Whoa, is that really it...?
(still confident)

493
00:26:32,724 --> 00:26:35,281
The aroma was already totally different right here.

494
00:26:35,306 --> 00:26:37,195
Yeah, completely different.

495
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:40,073
I didn't even need it brought all the way over.

496
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,515
This one has overwhelming depth,

497
00:26:42,540 --> 00:26:45,815
and this unique, slightly bitter astringency,

498
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:48,940
and that part really makes you feel its history.

499
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:53,653
Tendo, you look like you're about to cry right now.

500
00:26:53,678 --> 00:26:55,023
About to cry?

501
00:26:55,048 --> 00:26:56,073
Yeah, pretty much.

502
00:26:56,098 --> 00:26:58,086
It's her first time, you know.

503
00:26:58,111 --> 00:26:59,115
But it's okay.

504
00:26:59,140 --> 00:27:00,352
She might end up being the only one who got it right.

505
00:27:00,377 --> 00:27:01,995
Yeah, a solo victory.

506
00:27:02,020 --> 00:27:03,895
Tendo~!

507
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:05,657
You'll be fine.

508
00:27:05,682 --> 00:27:08,928
Unlike "lonely Tendo," in the other room...

509
00:27:08,953 --> 00:27:11,466
more and more people are gathering.

510
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:13,496
Oh!

511
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,113
Excuse us.

512
00:27:16,220 --> 00:27:17,868
Thank goodness.

513
00:27:18,003 --> 00:27:20,715
With this many people here, it's reassuring.

514
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:23,175
But Tendo is insanely confident.

515
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,995
Oh right, Tendo's the only one in the other room.

516
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:26,411
That's true.

517
00:27:31,016 --> 00:27:33,895
Tendo, with unshakable confidence.

518
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:36,421
Will she pull off a brilliant solo victory?

519
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:38,443
Next up,

520
00:27:38,468 --> 00:27:39,820
Here they come!

521
00:27:39,844 --> 00:27:40,669
They’re here!

522
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:42,127
Kis-My-Ft2!

523
00:27:42,152 --> 00:27:43,820
From Kis-My-Ft2,

524
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:45,155
Daisuke Fujigaya,

525
00:27:45,180 --> 00:27:46,000
Toshiya Miyata,

526
00:27:46,023 --> 00:27:48,241
and Yokoo Wataru

527
00:27:48,266 --> 00:27:52,479
Top idols whose overwhelming live performances have always captivated fans,

528
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:58,597
first-rank entertainers highly praised for their solo work in films and dramas.

529
00:27:59,577 --> 00:28:02,313
We nailed it last time. We really did.

530
00:28:02,338 --> 00:28:03,335
We got it right.

531
00:28:03,420 --> 00:28:06,000
In Kis-My-Ft2, the three older members...

532
00:28:06,316 --> 00:28:07,148
I see.

533
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:10,603
But even with three of you, you really can end up split.

534
00:28:10,628 --> 00:28:13,015
Still, we’ll probably decide fast without disagreeing,

535
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,389
and hit the answer right away.

536
00:28:14,414 --> 00:28:17,862
We’re top-tier, after all.

537
00:28:17,887 --> 00:28:23,837
Kis-My-Ft2 sound confident about wine. They start with glass A.

538
00:28:31,276 --> 00:28:34,276
Yokoo already knows, I can tell.

539
00:28:34,301 --> 00:28:35,181
Seriously?

540
00:28:35,205 --> 00:28:37,549
Or maybe he really doesn’t.

541
00:28:37,574 --> 00:28:41,127
Wait, which is it then?

542
00:28:41,152 --> 00:28:44,774
Yokoo sometimes makes that face even when he has no idea.

543
00:28:44,799 --> 00:28:46,096
I don’t know.

544
00:28:47,799 --> 00:28:51,292
Does Yokoo actually know the answer?

545
00:28:57,659 --> 00:28:58,576
What are you doing?

546
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:00,638
What are you doing!

547
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,575
What happened?

548
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,255
It went down the wrong way.

549
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:08,495
Careful there.

550
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:09,843
Now that I've hit forty.

551
00:29:10,379 --> 00:29:14,096
This still-active idol is choking and coughing like an old man.

552
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:18,475
The answer the three of them come up with is...

553
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,496
Ready, set

554
00:29:20,020 --> 00:29:21,075
A!

555
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:22,375
You’re kidding!

556
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:23,614
They split.

557
00:29:24,340 --> 00:29:26,231
We’ve got a split decision.

558
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:27,800
Then let's just go with A.

559
00:29:27,825 --> 00:29:29,100
Yeah, let's make it A.

560
00:29:29,207 --> 00:29:31,336
They split.

561
00:29:31,541 --> 00:29:34,305
(friends coming?)

562
00:29:37,208 --> 00:29:39,160
The smell of A was stronger

563
00:29:41,063 --> 00:29:45,071
But I felt B went down easier.

564
00:29:45,096 --> 00:29:49,988
But wasn't he coughing?

565
00:29:50,013 --> 00:29:52,261
Ok let's go for A

566
00:29:53,582 --> 00:29:57,756
Because I coughed

567
00:29:59,230 --> 00:30:03,201
Because of that you changed you mind?

568
00:30:03,476 --> 00:30:06,513
 She must be uncomfortable right now

569
00:30:06,537 --> 00:30:09,274
It's ok

570
00:30:09,625 --> 00:30:12,339
Kis-my-Ft2 also picked A.

571
00:30:12,364 --> 00:30:16,038
It seems A is the right answer.

572
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:19,642
Everyone, lock in your answers.

573
00:30:20,451 --> 00:30:21,713
Whoa!

574
00:30:22,349 --> 00:30:24,717
Thank goodness.

575
00:30:25,679 --> 00:30:27,158
What a relief.

576
00:30:27,411 --> 00:30:29,293
Man...

577
00:30:29,318 --> 00:30:32,797
Looks like A has the edge.

578
00:30:33,134 --> 00:30:40,658
(killing time)

579
00:30:44,776 --> 00:30:46,345
And lastly,

580
00:30:46,746 --> 00:30:48,029
Thanks for having us

581
00:30:48,780 --> 00:30:51,075
Here we are, the final round.

582
00:30:51,282 --> 00:30:53,075
From Fruits Zipper,

583
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:56,921
Suzuka Chinsei, Karen Matsumoto, and Yui Sakurai!

584
00:30:56,946 --> 00:30:59,980
With catchy songs and razor-sharp dance moves,

585
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,676
they've shot to nationwide fame,

586
00:31:01,740 --> 00:31:07,315
and just yesterday made their first appearance on the legendary New Year's Eve show, Kouhaku Uta Gassen.

587
00:31:07,340 --> 00:31:08,147
So, how about wine?

588
00:31:08,171 --> 00:31:09,467
I love wine.

589
00:31:09,492 --> 00:31:10,139
You do?

590
00:31:10,164 --> 00:31:14,138
Yeah, if everyone just goes with what I say, we should be fine.

591
00:31:14,163 --> 00:31:17,475
So even if you split, everyone should side with you, right?

592
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:21,101
I've actually never had wine before.

593
00:31:21,126 --> 00:31:23,595
So I'm kind of like, What do I even do?'

594
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:26,740
But I figured maybe I should just pick whichever one tastes better.

595
00:31:26,764 --> 00:31:27,794
Exactly!

596
00:31:27,819 --> 00:31:29,415
Wait, really? That works?

597
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:30,153
Yay!

598
00:31:30,415 --> 00:31:31,748
Alright then.

599
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:36,541
The confident Chinsei stands in the center,

600
00:31:40,754 --> 00:31:42,948
with Matsumoto, trying wine for the very first time,

601
00:31:43,260 --> 00:31:45,336
Will beginner's luck strike?

602
00:31:45,361 --> 00:31:47,438
One of you isn't drinking, right?

603
00:31:47,463 --> 00:31:48,375
That's right, I'm not.

604
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,807
I don't drink alcohol at all.

605
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:52,800
This is literally her first time ever.

606
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,346
Wine really is a first in her life.

607
00:31:58,954 --> 00:32:01,819
...seems first time

608
00:32:01,844 --> 00:32:06,891
Next, they try wine B, which only Tendo has chosen so far.

609
00:32:07,369 --> 00:32:11,729
Which one will the three of them choose?

610
00:32:11,754 --> 00:32:14,032
You guys are ok?

611
00:32:16,267 --> 00:32:18,795
Their final answer is...

612
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:20,000
Ready, and

613
00:32:20,675 --> 00:32:21,755
A!

614
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:23,527
Ohh!

615
00:32:24,701 --> 00:32:27,245
(could be in trouble)

616
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:32,941
Ohh!

617
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,975
Hard to believe that's their first time drinking it.

618
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,435
That's impressive!

619
00:32:36,460 --> 00:32:37,995
But that almost makes me more nervous.

620
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:40,525
Yeah, seriously.

621
00:32:40,708 --> 00:32:45,696
I see... is everyone okay with that?

622
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:57,875
When I drank B, I thought it smelled a bit off, so I figured A was the real one.

623
00:32:57,900 --> 00:32:58,726
Simple.

624
00:32:58,820 --> 00:33:00,483
Super concise.

625
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,447
Easy to understand.

626
00:33:02,472 --> 00:33:04,305
Tendo-san.

627
00:33:05,589 --> 00:33:07,235
(tired of waiting)

628
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:10,135
You are practically leaning over.

629
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:13,024
I feel incredibly awful right now.

630
00:33:13,049 --> 00:33:16,327
It is okay, Tendo-san.

631
00:33:16,352 --> 00:33:20,680
Fruits Zipper, who were totally in sync, also chose A.

632
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,208
Ready, and...

633
00:33:28,873 --> 00:33:31,495
Oh, there are people over there too.

634
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:35,128
This is no time to be saying 'Oh, there are people over there too.'

635
00:33:36,340 --> 00:33:38,680
Thank you all for your patience.

636
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:41,460
the correct answer will be the room the Ranking Master goes into.

637
00:33:41,485 --> 00:33:43,221
Please wait just a little longer.

638
00:33:47,025 --> 00:33:51,874
Fork in Fate: time for the results.

639
00:33:52,700 --> 00:33:54,799
Here we are.

640
00:34:01,739 --> 00:34:05,651
Alright then, let us open the door to the correct room.

641
00:34:05,676 --> 00:34:06,712
Please.

642
00:34:08,666 --> 00:34:10,515
Please.

643
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,172
The correct answer is...

644
00:34:23,540 --> 00:34:24,984
Is it A,

645
00:34:24,996 --> 00:34:29,133
or is B not to be underestimated?

646
00:34:42,071 --> 00:34:43,143
Huh?

647
00:34:43,207 --> 00:34:45,087
Seriously?

648
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:06,537
The correct answer is A.

649
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:13,380
In Check 1, the 1-million-yen wine was A.

650
00:35:14,412 --> 00:35:16,180
You were the only one who got it wrong.

651
00:35:16,205 --> 00:35:19,753
It is insanely awkward right now.

652
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:23,521
We are a team, you know.

653
00:35:23,546 --> 00:35:27,588
To be honest, I was leaning toward A.

654
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:33,595
The correct A was Château La Mission Haut-Brion.

655
00:35:34,465 --> 00:35:38,636
GACKT currently has an 81-win personal streak.

656
00:35:38,661 --> 00:35:43,957
Will he choose the correct A and extend his winning streak?

657
00:35:55,639 --> 00:36:00,326
Fork in Fate: GACKT's reveal.

658
00:36:03,621 --> 00:36:05,253
Here we go.

659
00:36:06,300 --> 00:36:08,258
So, which side is GACKT on?

660
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:15,051
Did GACKT get it right?

661
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,449
Let us find out.

662
00:36:25,140 --> 00:36:26,667
Look.

663
00:36:33,090 --> 00:36:35,092
Excellent!

664
00:36:37,295 --> 00:36:38,677
This time...

665
00:36:38,702 --> 00:36:43,301
this was the easiest challenge of all time

666
00:36:43,326 --> 00:36:44,873
How many nuts did you eat?!

667
00:36:44,899 --> 00:36:46,899
I was waiting a long time

668
00:36:49,006 --> 00:36:56,681
(nut counter)

669
00:36:56,706 --> 00:37:03,287
Relaxed enough to savor his nuts, his winning streak now reaches 82.

670
00:37:03,312 --> 00:37:08,475
GACKT gets off to a fantastic rocket start in 2026 as well.

671
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:13,297
Everyone else, except Tendo Emiko, splendidly kept their top-tier rating.

672
00:37:13,322 --> 00:37:20,805
Of course, the team that got it wrong will be treated accordingly.

673
00:37:20,830 --> 00:37:23,899
The people who answered correctly are back.

674
00:37:24,340 --> 00:37:26,840
These are the ones who guessed the 1-million-yen wine.

675
00:37:27,643 --> 00:37:29,761
GACKT, 82 straight wins.

676
00:37:31,129 --> 00:37:32,979
Congratulations.

677
00:37:33,649 --> 00:37:35,253
That was outstanding.

678
00:37:41,425 --> 00:37:44,362
Out of 8 groups, 7 got it right.

679
00:37:44,387 --> 00:37:46,214
Now, the ones who were wrong...

680
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:49,208
To the person who made a mistake...

681
00:37:49,233 --> 00:37:50,355
Please, come on in.

682
00:37:50,380 --> 00:37:52,268
Huh, we are going in from there?

683
00:37:52,293 --> 00:37:53,194
Huh?

684
00:37:54,872 --> 00:37:55,873
What ...?

685
00:37:55,899 --> 00:37:56,901
Crawling?

686
00:37:57,200 --> 00:38:00,015
Only one person got it wrong.

687
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,579
Here comes Tendo-san.

688
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:06,759
That is a grapevine branch.

689
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:09,053
Please take that with you and return to your seat.

690
00:38:10,060 --> 00:38:11,355
That was rough, huh?

691
00:38:11,380 --> 00:38:12,203
Fumi-san, I am sorry.

692
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:14,425
No, it is totally fine.

693
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,027
But you know...

694
00:38:16,052 --> 00:38:18,596
That was an awful time for you, was it not, Tendo-san?

695
00:38:19,900 --> 00:38:21,999
Do you have to put it like that?

696
00:38:23,020 --> 00:38:24,968
Hurry up and take off those slippers.

697
00:38:25,859 --> 00:38:26,557
Thank you.

698
00:38:26,850 --> 00:38:28,634
Oh, don't need these...

699
00:38:28,660 --> 00:38:30,074
thanks for your hard work.

700
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:32,394
She even threw the slippers.

701
00:38:32,540 --> 00:38:34,841
Why throw the slippers?

702
00:38:35,713 --> 00:38:37,194
Now, for the next check...

703
00:38:37,220 --> 00:38:38,449
Here is the second check.

704
00:38:40,494 --> 00:38:41,819
It is 'tate' choreographed sword-fighting.

705
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:44,860
'Tate' is, in plays and films...

706
00:38:45,050 --> 00:38:48,174
the term for choreographed fighting scenes mainly using swords.

707
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:52,530
It demands high-level skills: speed, intensity, acting ability...

708
00:38:52,555 --> 00:38:58,703
This time, we want you to judge the performances of the people being cut down in tate.

709
00:38:58,728 --> 00:39:02,081
For Check 2: tate

710
00:39:02,106 --> 00:39:06,711
We have the cooperation of Japan Action Enterprise.

711
00:39:06,736 --> 00:39:10,295
It was founded by international star Shinichi Chiba in 1970

712
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:15,634
and is a prestigious school that has trained action stars, including Hiroyuki Sanada in the past.

713
00:39:15,660 --> 00:39:21,875
The correct answer is this top-tier period-drama tate group, each with over 30 years of experience.

714
00:39:21,900 --> 00:39:24,570
These four have appeared in famed period dramas like the Taiga series,

715
00:39:24,595 --> 00:39:29,934
'Abarenbo Shogun', 'Onihei', 'Hankacho', 'Mito Komon', and many more.

716
00:39:29,959 --> 00:39:32,536
Between the four of them, they have been 'cut down'

717
00:39:32,561 --> 00:39:35,244
over 20,000 times,

718
00:39:35,256 --> 00:39:37,875
making them superhuman-level victims.

719
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:44,223
And to compare, the other side is a young tate group with much less period-drama experience.

720
00:39:44,248 --> 00:39:50,421
They are gradually building experience and, between the four of them, have been cut about 800 times.

721
00:39:50,446 --> 00:39:55,301
Oh wow... that's still a lot of times!

722
00:39:55,326 --> 00:39:58,525
This time, it will be set up like a period-drama episode,

723
00:39:58,550 --> 00:40:01,180
and you will compare the two tate performances.

724
00:40:01,205 --> 00:40:05,760
We have invited the big bad boss who leads these doomed underlings.

725
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:07,605
Here he is. Please come in.

726
00:40:10,780 --> 00:40:12,910
This is Satoshi Jinbo.

727
00:40:18,079 --> 00:40:22,109
Jinbo-san has appeared in many period dramas,

728
00:40:22,139 --> 00:40:25,189
including year-long historical epics.

729
00:40:25,220 --> 00:40:27,191
Jinbo, how was it for you doing these things again?

730
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:30,995
Doing stage combat again really reminded me how deep and complex it is.

731
00:40:33,164 --> 00:40:37,768
And now, the boss who takes down Jinbo's gang of villains, the star of today's show...

732
00:40:40,146 --> 00:40:42,640
Ryuji Harada.

733
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:50,600
You all know Mr. Harada, ...

734
00:40:50,660 --> 00:40:52,654
He played Sukesan in 'Mito Komon', among many other roles,

735
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:54,800
and has appeared in countless period dramas.

736
00:40:55,336 --> 00:40:58,935
Seike Kazuto from Toei Tsurugikai, who has supervised sword-fighting choreography on many period dramas,

737
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:00,491
has said this about him:

738
00:41:00,841 --> 00:41:03,169
'No one else can move at that speed.'

739
00:41:03,194 --> 00:41:06,397
and that he has an aesthetic sense that really sets him apart from other actors.

740
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,575
He is showered with praise.

741
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:13,579
They say he is one of the top five period-drama actors for sword-fighting work.

742
00:41:13,604 --> 00:41:16,907
See? It turned out just like I taught you, right?

743
00:41:17,220 --> 00:41:18,455
That is true.

744
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:20,820
Thank you.

745
00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:22,932
How did it feel actually doing it this time?

746
00:41:23,083 --> 00:41:29,308
I think in stage combat the one who gets cut has the more important role.

747
00:41:29,333 --> 00:41:30,020
I see.

748
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:33,236
More important than the one doing the cutting, you mean?

749
00:41:34,692 --> 00:41:38,075
The people being tested are these familiar faces.

750
00:41:38,100 --> 00:41:42,233
For them, telling top-level sword-fighting apart should be an easy question.

751
00:41:42,258 --> 00:41:45,935
Alright, representatives, please step forward.

752
00:41:54,245 --> 00:41:58,833
They will be watching this check in groups, all at the same time.

753
00:42:00,885 --> 00:42:04,849
We will start with these four groups.

754
00:42:05,389 --> 00:42:14,131
Mao Daichi, a legendary top star of the Takarazuka Revue and still a first-class entertainer on the front lines.

755
00:42:14,155 --> 00:42:18,104
Back in my Takarazuka days I did play the one doing the cutting,

756
00:42:18,116 --> 00:42:22,615
but being the one who gets cut is a bit...

757
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,442
You need to study that side of it.

758
00:42:25,467 --> 00:42:30,134
Emiko Kaminuma, celebrating the 55th anniversary of her debut this year,

759
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:36,195
a Kansai-based host and singer, currently ranked as a mid-level celebrity on this show.

760
00:42:36,220 --> 00:42:38,452
Sorry to bring up such an old story,

761
00:42:38,476 --> 00:42:42,134
but 48 years ago...

762
00:42:43,786 --> 00:42:45,305
That was rude...

763
00:42:45,329 --> 00:42:48,265
I used to go to Uzuno-san's film studio every single week.

764
00:42:48,290 --> 00:42:50,935
You honestly do not remember that, do you?

765
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:53,455
I do remember!

766
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:55,735
You remember things from when you were young really well.

767
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:59,810
Better than remembering what you ate yesterday.

768
00:42:59,835 --> 00:43:01,421
Koda Kumi

769
00:43:01,446 --> 00:43:04,246
She has three albums which sold over 1 million copies.

770
00:43:04,271 --> 00:43:09,075
A top rated artist in Japan who has won numerous awards.

771
00:43:09,100 --> 00:43:11,822
I have been doing traditional dance since I was three.

772
00:43:11,847 --> 00:43:15,659
I have also had the chance to perform sword dances,

773
00:43:15,684 --> 00:43:19,555
so I really feel I cannot afford to get this wrong.

774
00:43:19,580 --> 00:43:20,764
I absolutely want to get the right answer.

775
00:43:20,789 --> 00:43:22,239
It is just that...

776
00:43:22,264 --> 00:43:24,401
When you start saying things like 'it is just that' to everyone...

777
00:43:24,839 --> 00:43:27,944
I am afraid I will get dazzled by how beautiful the one doing the cutting looks.

778
00:43:27,970 --> 00:43:29,707
The person swinging the sword, I mean.

779
00:43:29,732 --> 00:43:31,839
Kis-My-Ft2.

780
00:43:31,860 --> 00:43:35,044
Hamamori Yuta, Kento Senga, and Takashi Nikaido.

781
00:43:35,069 --> 00:43:40,351
A top idol group whose New Year countdown concert was a huge success.

782
00:43:40,376 --> 00:43:43,255
We once had people from Japan Action Enterprise

783
00:43:43,281 --> 00:43:46,466
personally teach us.

784
00:43:46,490 --> 00:43:49,234
They said you cannot make it look good unless,

785
00:43:49,259 --> 00:43:51,503
even as the one getting cut, you put yourself in the cutter's position.

786
00:43:51,528 --> 00:43:53,935
But you are an idiot, you think such about such deep things?

787
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:55,193
Of course!

788
00:43:55,300 --> 00:43:58,936
I will be cut in absolutely perfect fashion.

789
00:43:58,961 --> 00:44:05,042
Which one is Kirara - the veteran with 30 years of stage combat experience? A or B?

790
00:44:05,067 --> 00:44:08,743
This challenge is presented as a period-drama scene, with acting before and after the fight.

791
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:11,945
Please consider it together with us.

792
00:44:12,783 --> 00:44:16,388
If you want a closer look, you can come up to around here.

793
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:19,023
If you are fine where you are, you can stay put.

794
00:44:19,048 --> 00:44:21,892
First, fight A.

795
00:44:36,958 --> 00:44:38,462
Princess...

796
00:44:38,488 --> 00:44:43,795
the mountain path is rough from here. I must ask you to leave the carriage and walk.

797
00:44:43,820 --> 00:44:48,624
If we do not hurry, the Hamada clan's men may catch up with us.

798
00:44:54,845 --> 00:44:57,235
(heroine at 3pm comedian Kanade)

799
00:44:57,260 --> 00:45:00,495
Ryuji, I am sorry to keep causing you such hardship.

800
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:03,561
Think nothing of it. Come, let us go.

801
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:11,757
Princess Kanade, you have nowhere left to run.

802
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:14,328
Damn, they have cut us off.

803
00:45:14,780 --> 00:45:18,060
I will not let you lay a single finger on the princess.

804
00:45:23,260 --> 00:45:24,786
Are you alright?

805
00:45:24,830 --> 00:45:26,838
Leave this to me.

806
00:45:29,039 --> 00:45:30,423
Ryuji...

807
00:45:30,620 --> 00:45:32,732
Your fate is sealed.

808
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,974
Men, to me!

809
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:40,975
On my life,

810
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:42,888
I will take the princess back!

811
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:46,555
Men, attack!

812
00:46:16,044 --> 00:46:19,093
As expected of you, Ryuji.

813
00:46:19,260 --> 00:46:22,279
But do not think this is the end.

814
00:46:44,037 --> 00:46:45,701
Ryuji..

815
00:46:45,727 --> 00:46:48,379
That's was excellent!

816
00:46:48,404 --> 00:46:49,372
Still...

817
00:46:49,526 --> 00:46:51,634
there might be more

818
00:46:51,660 --> 00:46:52,683
We must hurry on.

819
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:55,853
Walk?

820
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:58,019
Please.

821
00:47:04,421 --> 00:47:07,257
You could really feel that 'I am ready to die' emotion there.

822
00:47:07,282 --> 00:47:10,494
They took those blows beautifully.

823
00:47:10,519 --> 00:47:13,158
Next is fight B.

824
00:47:13,183 --> 00:47:16,166
We start from the ninja's entrance.

825
00:47:16,460 --> 00:47:17,554
Ryuji!

826
00:47:17,820 --> 00:47:19,720
Your fate is sealed.

827
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:22,934
Men, to me!

828
00:47:26,400 --> 00:47:30,457
I will get the princess back, even if it costs me my life!

829
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:33,359
Men!

830
00:47:33,520 --> 00:47:35,141
Attack!

831
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:09,738
Impressive as always, Ryuji

832
00:48:10,140 --> 00:48:12,376
But don't think it's over yet.

833
00:48:28,794 --> 00:48:30,594
What the hell?

834
00:48:30,620 --> 00:48:32,277
So annoying.

835
00:48:55,180 --> 00:48:58,191
Ryuji! Thank you so much!

836
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:00,120
There might be still enemies hiding.

837
00:49:00,740 --> 00:49:01,837
Let's hurry on.

838
00:49:01,863 --> 00:49:02,466
Right.

839
00:49:05,646 --> 00:49:07,719
You took too long!

840
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:09,975
Hahaha... took too long!

841
00:49:14,840 --> 00:49:17,892
The acting in the second half dragged on a bit too long...

842
00:49:17,917 --> 00:49:19,323
Yeah, kinda.

843
00:49:19,348 --> 00:49:22,540
Jun, by the way, which one do you think it is?

844
00:49:22,565 --> 00:49:29,666
In A, it felt like they were acting in a way that made it easier for Harada-san to land the cut.

845
00:49:29,691 --> 00:49:32,836
And you two from Fruits Zipper, which do you think it was?

846
00:49:33,059 --> 00:49:34,280
I thought it was team B.

847
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:36,707
I thought it was B as well.

848
00:49:36,820 --> 00:49:37,720
We're split on this one.

849
00:49:37,844 --> 00:49:39,594
with the three of us split like this...

850
00:49:39,620 --> 00:49:42,560
I was leaning toward A.

851
00:49:42,560 --> 00:49:44,381
The two next to me were both saying B.

852
00:49:44,406 --> 00:49:45,555
Tendo-san...

853
00:49:45,580 --> 00:49:49,487
I've also done period dramas, actually,

854
00:49:49,512 --> 00:49:52,360
so I think it was B.

855
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:54,685
When they delivered that slash,

856
00:49:54,710 --> 00:49:56,940
the way they slowly staggered back,

857
00:49:57,060 --> 00:49:59,760
it really looked like they'd been cut through the torso.

858
00:49:59,780 --> 00:50:03,420
With A I somehow got more of a dynamic feel.

859
00:50:03,445 --> 00:50:05,125
So A. I'm going with A.

860
00:50:05,150 --> 00:50:06,038
Got it.

861
00:50:06,063 --> 00:50:06,940
Takeshi, what about you?

862
00:50:07,040 --> 00:50:08,035
B.

863
00:50:08,060 --> 00:50:08,995
And you?

864
00:50:09,020 --> 00:50:14,395
Well, A definitely had better tempo and flowed more smoothly,

865
00:50:14,420 --> 00:50:18,493
but my eyes kept going to B's opponent and the way they handled the distance,

866
00:50:18,519 --> 00:50:20,745
so that's why I'm choosing B

867
00:50:20,770 --> 00:50:21,909
Understood.

868
00:50:22,452 --> 00:50:30,293
So which was it for Kirara, the veteran with thirty years in the business: A or B?

869
00:50:30,318 --> 00:50:35,469
First up, Daichi Mao, who has sword-fighting experience from her Takarazuka days.

870
00:50:35,824 --> 00:50:37,006
Here we go.

871
00:50:37,755 --> 00:50:40,170
Which way will Dai-san go?

872
00:50:42,682 --> 00:50:45,021
Her answer is...

873
00:50:46,877 --> 00:50:49,275
Oh, you can really see Dai-san's eye for this.

874
00:50:49,300 --> 00:50:51,347
You're in agreement.

875
00:50:53,817 --> 00:50:57,229
Everyone's teamwork is really in sync,

876
00:50:57,254 --> 00:51:01,060
and even when I watched them lying there after being cut,

877
00:51:01,591 --> 00:51:05,235
there was absolutely no sense of them breathing,

878
00:51:05,260 --> 00:51:07,594
which I thought was amazing.

879
00:51:07,620 --> 00:51:09,055
Exactly.

880
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:10,509
I see.

881
00:51:10,534 --> 00:51:12,455
We on set didn't even notice that.

882
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:14,355
You focus on totally different things.

883
00:51:14,380 --> 00:51:15,672
Wonderful.

884
00:51:15,823 --> 00:51:18,884
Daichi Mao chooses B.

885
00:51:21,778 --> 00:51:25,460
She wants to somehow make up for her partner Tendo's mistake.

886
00:51:25,485 --> 00:51:27,500
Ordinary Emi Kaminuma.

887
00:51:27,525 --> 00:51:30,787
I really want to keep my status as a 'normal celebrity'.

888
00:51:31,420 --> 00:51:33,148
Her answer is...

889
00:51:33,420 --> 00:51:34,925
B.

890
00:51:39,863 --> 00:51:44,080
From the setup you could see they were fully committed to being the one who gets cut down.

891
00:51:44,500 --> 00:51:46,500
I thought, wow, that's what a real veteran looks like.

892
00:51:46,720 --> 00:51:48,091
I'm confident.

893
00:51:48,165 --> 00:51:50,240
Thank you very much.

894
00:51:54,211 --> 00:51:57,782
She never forgets to say thank you, appreciating everything

895
00:51:57,807 --> 00:52:00,702
She is headed to the room Daichi Mao is waiting in: B

896
00:52:04,676 --> 00:52:06,714
Thank...you...so...much

897
00:52:06,740 --> 00:52:08,443
Definitely B

898
00:52:13,864 --> 00:52:17,830
Koda Kumi has been doing kenbu since 3 years old

899
00:52:18,173 --> 00:52:20,137
Here she comes

900
00:52:23,206 --> 00:52:24,956
Can she remain 1st class?

901
00:52:25,063 --> 00:52:26,705
Correct answer is...

902
00:52:26,963 --> 00:52:28,497
B.

903
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:30,831
Another B.

904
00:52:31,380 --> 00:52:33,151
The streak continues.

905
00:52:35,018 --> 00:52:38,910
Looking at the lingering aftereffect once they'd been cut,

906
00:52:38,935 --> 00:52:41,015
I felt like they really paid attention to the details.

907
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:43,602
Her opinion's a little different from Hiromi-sama's, though.

908
00:52:43,627 --> 00:52:44,260
True.

909
00:52:44,340 --> 00:52:45,914
We'll see which way it goes.

910
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:49,955
Since both of you were saying B,

911
00:52:49,980 --> 00:52:54,040
I kind of started remembering it that way too.

912
00:52:54,060 --> 00:52:55,839
So, B.

913
00:52:56,839 --> 00:52:58,464
Not that my own reactions have anything to do with it.

914
00:52:58,490 --> 00:52:59,209
Yeah, yeah, that's right.

915
00:52:59,234 --> 00:53:01,945
Hiromi-san, that has absolutely nothing to do with it though.

916
00:53:02,265 --> 00:53:04,450
So it's the opposite of Hiromi Go.

917
00:53:04,475 --> 00:53:06,798
Takada also chooses B.

918
00:53:08,451 --> 00:53:09,809
Whoa.

919
00:53:10,279 --> 00:53:11,933
All right!

920
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:15,235
I thought if Taishi-san was in there, then B had to be OK.

921
00:53:15,260 --> 00:53:18,524
Because you two are here I have confidence

922
00:53:20,230 --> 00:53:25,809
Kis-My-Ft2 have been trained directly by the professional group

923
00:53:27,487 --> 00:53:29,487
Here comes...

924
00:53:29,754 --> 00:53:30,974
Which will they pick?

925
00:53:30,999 --> 00:53:33,276
Kis-My-Ft2 split their answer last time...

926
00:53:36,349 --> 00:53:39,078
This one cannot be wrong

927
00:53:44,809 --> 00:53:47,123
split

928
00:53:49,359 --> 00:53:53,257
A was smooth...wasn't it?

929
00:53:54,479 --> 00:53:55,575
For real?

930
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:57,279
What really decided it for me

931
00:53:57,291 --> 00:53:59,525
was how they left a wide acting area

932
00:53:59,537 --> 00:54:01,880
for the showdown between Jimbo-san and Harada-san.

933
00:54:02,380 --> 00:54:03,499
B.

934
00:54:04,540 --> 00:54:07,719
You were really watching closely.

935
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:10,055
I'm the only one left, so I'll go with B to match you.

936
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:13,995
This really felt like B to me, you could hear it in their voice, it was amazing.

937
00:54:14,020 --> 00:54:15,004
That's important.

938
00:54:15,820 --> 00:54:17,619
All right, I'll make this one B.

939
00:54:17,940 --> 00:54:21,020
This really brings back how we used to learn it, huh.

940
00:54:21,420 --> 00:54:23,690
Kis-My also chose B.

941
00:54:23,715 --> 00:54:26,669
Off to Room B, where the lovely ladies are waiting.

942
00:54:36,114 --> 00:54:37,896
Right!?

943
00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:40,640
So far, everyone has picked B.

944
00:54:40,900 --> 00:54:45,015
So which one is actually correct?

945
00:54:47,017 --> 00:54:49,660
Check No. 2: Swordplay.

946
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:52,656
Up to this point, everyone has gone with B.

947
00:54:53,540 --> 00:54:57,427
Next up, these four groups will take the test.

948
00:55:01,598 --> 00:55:03,219
Kimura Tae.

949
00:55:03,244 --> 00:55:06,185
She plays everything from serious roles to comedy.

950
00:55:06,210 --> 00:55:10,415
A top-tier actor, famous as a brilliant supporting performer.

951
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:13,209
People think I move really slowly all the time, but...

952
00:55:13,234 --> 00:55:15,320
They once asked me if I wanted to join the Japan Action Club.

953
00:55:15,345 --> 00:55:16,952
I kind of got scouted for it.

954
00:55:17,359 --> 00:55:18,930
They said, 'You've got talent, why not join?'

955
00:55:18,955 --> 00:55:19,640
For real?

956
00:55:20,160 --> 00:55:22,986
You really do give off that slow, laid-back vibe though.

957
00:55:23,011 --> 00:55:26,990
But I can actually move fast.

958
00:55:28,923 --> 00:55:30,497
FRUITS ZIPPER.

959
00:55:30,524 --> 00:55:31,666
Nakagawa Runa.

960
00:55:31,691 --> 00:55:33,103
Manaka Mana.

961
00:55:33,128 --> 00:55:35,042
With a total number of TikTok views that's just insane,

962
00:55:35,067 --> 00:55:39,177
they're a top idol group on a whole different level.

963
00:55:39,202 --> 00:55:41,079
Since we dance and perform a lot,

964
00:55:41,103 --> 00:55:43,034
I think we should look at how dynamic

965
00:55:43,060 --> 00:55:45,608
their movements are and all that.

966
00:55:45,992 --> 00:55:47,430
That's what I'm thinking.

967
00:55:48,299 --> 00:55:49,373
Yeah.

968
00:55:52,615 --> 00:55:54,275
Batteries.

969
00:55:54,300 --> 00:55:57,714
They were runners-up at the M-1 Grand Prix the year before last and blew up nationwide.

970
00:55:57,740 --> 00:56:02,264
Top-class entertainers who embody both M-1-level comedy and mainstream appeal.

971
00:56:02,726 --> 00:56:04,898
We've seen a lot in theaters too,

972
00:56:04,923 --> 00:56:08,356
like tons of people getting slashed in skits and stuff.

973
00:56:08,380 --> 00:56:09,823
There's just one thing I'm a bit worried about.

974
00:56:09,848 --> 00:56:11,378
Right at the beginning, when it first came up on screen,

975
00:56:11,430 --> 00:56:13,703
Ace was like, 'How are you even supposed to read that kanji?'

976
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:16,773
I've never really seen those characters before.

977
00:56:16,798 --> 00:56:21,735
And GACKT, currently on an 82-game personal winning streak,

978
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:25,554
has appeared in many period dramas, including historical epics.

979
00:56:26,340 --> 00:56:29,395
The people I've gone up against in sword-fighting scenes have all been first-rate pros.

980
00:56:29,419 --> 00:56:30,134
Right.

981
00:56:30,269 --> 00:56:31,688
So there's no mistaking it.

982
00:56:32,040 --> 00:56:32,888
Is that so?

983
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:34,657
You're confident about this one too?

984
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:37,898
Did you eat before coming here?

985
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:41,464
You could speak up a bit more, you know.

986
00:56:42,100 --> 00:56:43,369
You're really, uh, something today.

987
00:56:43,394 --> 00:56:47,575
You're being super harsh to literally everyone.

988
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,400
No, I'm not.

989
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:52,140
First, the swordplay team A.

990
00:56:54,780 --> 00:56:56,600
For everyone watching at home,

991
00:56:56,865 --> 00:57:01,117
let us share some tips on how to spot the correct one.

992
00:57:02,060 --> 00:57:04,160
If they're just standing there getting cut, they're still green.

993
00:57:04,493 --> 00:57:09,280
The veterans rush in to attack and then get cut down themselves.

994
00:57:09,799 --> 00:57:15,838
They also have the skill to move in perfect sync so the lead can strike at just the right moment.

995
00:57:16,033 --> 00:57:20,346
Keeping that in mind, watch closely.

996
00:57:20,880 --> 00:57:23,762
Men, attack!

997
00:57:52,480 --> 00:57:57,474
And the evil boss is safely taken down as well.

998
00:58:08,117 --> 00:58:11,265
Next, swordplay team B.

999
00:58:12,288 --> 00:58:14,557
Face me!

1000
00:58:18,880 --> 00:58:21,916
Men, charge!

1001
00:58:52,824 --> 00:59:01,180
The evil boss held out stubbornly until the very end, but was finally defeated.

1002
00:59:05,700 --> 00:59:08,824
We're in the middle of a special here!

1003
00:59:17,687 --> 00:59:19,905
But this is really tough, isn't it?

1004
00:59:19,930 --> 00:59:22,017
Yeah, super hard.

1005
00:59:22,859 --> 00:59:28,472
First, GACKT, who just extended his winning streak to 82.

1006
00:59:29,529 --> 00:59:34,494
How did he arrive at his answer this time?

1007
00:59:34,519 --> 00:59:37,910
Just talking about the timing of getting cut,

1008
00:59:38,380 --> 00:59:41,448
the veterans are better at matching their timing.

1009
00:59:41,920 --> 00:59:43,446
They don't sit there and wait, you know?

1010
00:59:43,471 --> 00:59:45,815
Instead of waiting for the strike

1011
00:59:45,840 --> 00:59:48,117
and then trying to match it themselves,

1012
00:59:48,142 --> 00:59:53,756
they have the skill to let getting cut happen as a completely natural flow.

1013
00:59:58,161 --> 01:00:01,120
Once again, GACKT is totally composed.

1014
01:00:01,620 --> 01:00:07,256
So which did he choose, A or B?

1015
01:00:09,860 --> 01:00:12,499
And actress Kimura Tae, who's secretly quick on her feet,

1016
01:00:12,579 --> 01:00:14,820
was she able to pick out the first-rate sword fighters?

1017
01:00:15,680 --> 01:00:17,784
Ah, right now, Mizu-chan...

1018
01:00:22,119 --> 01:00:23,962
What answer did you give?

1019
01:00:24,050 --> 01:00:25,000
Ready, set...

1020
01:00:27,839 --> 01:00:29,653
Looks like we're split.

1021
01:00:29,678 --> 01:00:30,890
Yeah,they're divided.

1022
01:00:31,465 --> 01:00:33,116
They split on this one.

1023
01:00:33,620 --> 01:00:36,560
The part where they came down from the roof and rolled along the ground,

1024
01:00:36,910 --> 01:00:38,960
that bit made me think A as well.

1025
01:00:38,985 --> 01:00:43,235
With A, I really felt that veteran presence.

1026
01:00:43,260 --> 01:00:47,043
The B team felt fresher, like they were younger.

1027
01:00:47,068 --> 01:00:47,980
I'm going with A.

1028
01:00:48,700 --> 01:00:49,298
Really?

1029
01:00:49,380 --> 01:00:50,661
Let's choose A.

1030
01:00:51,460 --> 01:00:52,756
You're sure about that?

1031
01:00:52,983 --> 01:00:56,619
Yeah, that moment made me think, 'Oh, it's probably that side,' too.

1032
01:00:56,644 --> 01:01:00,616
So we ended up disagreeing with Mitsuumi-sama, who's still left in.

1033
01:01:00,820 --> 01:01:01,784
Yeah.

1034
01:01:02,520 --> 01:01:05,698
They decide to respect the opinion of Ino, star of the new drama,

1035
01:01:05,780 --> 01:01:08,280
And now, for the first time here, they pick A.

1036
01:01:08,553 --> 01:01:11,177
Heading into an empty room.

1037
01:01:15,540 --> 01:01:17,074
There's no one here.

1038
01:01:17,940 --> 01:01:19,396
Oh crap.

1039
01:01:19,685 --> 01:01:21,955
(suddenly anxious)

1040
01:01:21,980 --> 01:01:23,079
No way!

1041
01:01:23,190 --> 01:01:25,048
Huh? What? Seriously?

1042
01:01:29,371 --> 01:01:31,493
You have correct eyes yes?

1043
01:01:31,518 --> 01:01:35,185
Yeah, this is kind of scary, but I thought it was A

1044
01:01:35,758 --> 01:01:41,840
These three are top-tier idols from FRUITS ZIPPER, with a Tokyo Dome concert coming up next month.

1045
01:01:43,240 --> 01:01:44,132
All right, here we go.

1046
01:01:47,224 --> 01:01:49,321
And the answer they chose is...

1047
01:01:52,952 --> 01:01:54,306
Same!

1048
01:01:55,180 --> 01:01:56,860
Whoa, we're kind of split on this one, but...

1049
01:01:57,904 --> 01:01:58,581
Huh?

1050
01:02:01,217 --> 01:02:03,795
There’s nothing to argue about now, everyone picked A.

1051
01:02:03,820 --> 01:02:05,855
The voice, like, the deepness to it.

1052
01:02:05,880 --> 01:02:07,403
Yeah, totally.

1053
01:02:08,120 --> 01:02:10,295
Their voice just kind of...

1054
01:02:10,320 --> 01:02:13,432
That part really felt weighty, you know? Like it had gravitas.

1055
01:02:13,456 --> 01:02:15,012
That veteran vibe.

1056
01:02:15,038 --> 01:02:17,208
So it might be A

1057
01:02:17,233 --> 01:02:19,669
Man, when it gets like this I honestly have no idea anymore.

1058
01:02:19,694 --> 01:02:25,340
FRUITS ZIPPER, who now also act on the side, all unanimously chose A.

1059
01:02:25,639 --> 01:02:28,673
At this point, the A room has suddenly gotten packed.

1060
01:02:29,400 --> 01:02:30,792
Ready, and...

1061
01:02:35,284 --> 01:02:38,028
The teams are split!

1062
01:02:38,908 --> 01:02:41,095
(even more anxious)

1063
01:02:41,119 --> 01:02:42,773
We're divided.

1064
01:02:43,000 --> 01:02:44,095
Split decision.

1065
01:02:44,120 --> 01:02:45,385
You’re kidding.

1066
01:02:50,305 --> 01:02:52,305
He's eating something again

1067
01:02:56,581 --> 01:03:00,012
Why do we have to watch this?

1068
01:03:00,037 --> 01:03:01,711
The eating scene.

1069
01:03:02,245 --> 01:03:07,116
Batteries cannot afford to blow it in front of their great senior, Atsushi.

1070
01:03:07,141 --> 01:03:08,699
I hope they all match.

1071
01:03:09,960 --> 01:03:11,793
What did they choose?

1072
01:03:12,260 --> 01:03:13,369
One, two...

1073
01:03:14,140 --> 01:03:14,976
Oh!

1074
01:03:15,580 --> 01:03:16,440
Whaaat!

1075
01:03:16,480 --> 01:03:17,498
Nice, they matched.

1076
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:19,652
For real?

1077
01:03:21,060 --> 01:03:24,920
With B, it honestly felt like you could almost see the blood.

1078
01:03:25,060 --> 01:03:25,820
That intense?

1079
01:03:26,280 --> 01:03:28,280
Yeah, it was that sharp, that powerful.

1080
01:03:28,680 --> 01:03:30,405
The realism, or rather the impact, too.

1081
01:03:30,500 --> 01:03:31,820
B definitely had more of that.

1082
01:03:31,880 --> 01:03:33,080
They were clearly different.

1083
01:03:33,960 --> 01:03:36,280
But in the end, it's up to the people on set.

1084
01:03:36,300 --> 01:03:38,860
All right, so you two are going with B.

1085
01:03:40,180 --> 01:03:44,160
The two from Batteries choose B, a different answer from senior Atsushi.

1086
01:03:46,840 --> 01:03:49,701
I'm so awkward at this, first time going through this door.

1087
01:03:49,725 --> 01:03:51,466
Ohh.

1088
01:03:51,859 --> 01:03:52,580
Thank goodness.

1089
01:03:52,750 --> 01:03:54,754
What a relief.

1090
01:03:54,779 --> 01:03:55,500
So glad.

1091
01:03:56,030 --> 01:03:59,313
(now risky)

1092
01:03:59,340 --> 01:04:01,151
You’ve got to be kidding.

1093
01:04:01,779 --> 01:04:03,214
If we can win with this...

1094
01:04:03,239 --> 01:04:08,711
So which one is correct, A or B?

1095
01:04:16,441 --> 01:04:18,312
Stand by for the answer.

1096
01:04:18,337 --> 01:04:21,874
Is it A, or is it B?

1097
01:04:22,997 --> 01:04:27,961
The fateful crossroads: time for the results.

1098
01:04:28,580 --> 01:04:31,367
All right, here we are.

1099
01:04:32,560 --> 01:04:34,008
Here it comes.

1100
01:04:34,200 --> 01:04:35,180
It's here, it's here!

1101
01:04:35,200 --> 01:04:37,714
This is intense.

1102
01:04:37,739 --> 01:04:39,396
Please

1103
01:04:39,420 --> 01:04:43,262
We will now open the door to the correct room.

1104
01:04:48,084 --> 01:04:51,053
This is nerve-racking.

1105
01:04:53,120 --> 01:04:54,891
Please...

1106
01:05:04,180 --> 01:05:05,921
The correct answer is...

1107
01:05:37,359 --> 01:05:39,855
The correct answer was B.

1108
01:05:42,360 --> 01:05:44,607
There was a little bit of a fake-out in there.

1109
01:05:44,632 --> 01:05:46,612
Nice faking!

1110
01:05:47,819 --> 01:05:50,075
As expected of you.

1111
01:05:50,310 --> 01:05:55,151
They were completely different.

1112
01:05:55,176 --> 01:06:00,205
Shock!

1113
01:06:00,230 --> 01:06:02,024
No way!

1114
01:06:02,049 --> 01:06:10,044
Will the ever-confident GACKT-sama choose the correct B and extend his annual winning streak?

1115
01:06:12,185 --> 01:06:16,861
The fateful crossroads: GACKT's answer.

1116
01:06:17,716 --> 01:06:26,942
Well, Gak-chan is probably in there too...

1117
01:06:28,998 --> 01:06:35,170
Let's find out. Okay, here we go.

1118
01:06:39,136 --> 01:06:41,100
All right, he's in.

1119
01:06:43,332 --> 01:06:46,002
Wow, that's insane.

1120
01:06:51,380 --> 01:06:53,435
This was way too easy.

1121
01:06:53,460 --> 01:06:55,075
Yeah, it was ridiculously easy.

1122
01:06:55,100 --> 01:06:57,975
Weren't there a ton of correct-choosers this time?

1123
01:06:58,000 --> 01:07:01,179
But the A side had quite a few too.

1124
01:07:01,360 --> 01:07:02,573
There are like three groups in there.

1125
01:07:02,600 --> 01:07:03,180
Seriously?

1126
01:07:03,700 --> 01:07:07,656
Yeah, that’s pretty bad.

1127
01:07:07,681 --> 01:07:14,130
GACKT-sama nails it with ease and reaches 83 straight wins.

1128
01:07:14,920 --> 01:07:17,697
We have two teams who did pretty terribly, though.

1129
01:07:17,800 --> 01:07:22,705
Up next, an even more disastrous incident explodes onto the scene.

1130
01:07:23,034 --> 01:07:25,920
Okay, all the players who got it right have returned.

1131
01:07:26,080 --> 01:07:27,344
Thanks for your hard work.

1132
01:07:27,562 --> 01:07:34,992
Welcomed by Mr. Harada, Mr. Ichio, Mr. Katate, and our first-class troupe, the winners are making their entrance.

1133
01:07:35,017 --> 01:07:36,155
Congratulations.

1134
01:07:36,880 --> 01:07:39,005
You all did brilliantly.

1135
01:07:39,030 --> 01:07:40,495
And now, for those who got it wrong...

1136
01:07:40,520 --> 01:07:42,425
Wrong-answer team, come on in.

1137
01:07:43,920 --> 01:07:46,533
Instead of applause,

1138
01:07:46,545 --> 01:07:54,437
this time you'll be welcomed with cold stares from Harada-san, Jimbo-san, Kanade-san, and our top-tier squad.

1139
01:07:54,960 --> 01:07:56,775
So frustrating.

1140
01:07:56,800 --> 01:08:00,376
Our incorrect-answer group has returned.

1141
01:08:04,680 --> 01:08:09,505
When this many groups get it right, you have to say the professionals live up to their reputation.

1142
01:08:09,530 --> 01:08:13,565
Once you actually go up against the veterans, you can really tell they're on a different level.

1143
01:08:13,590 --> 01:08:14,590
I see.

1144
01:08:15,770 --> 01:08:17,354
You dragged it out too long.

1145
01:08:17,380 --> 01:08:18,541
Sorry about that.

1146
01:08:21,698 --> 01:08:23,813
We really didn't need you

1147
01:08:23,839 --> 01:08:24,898
What do you mean?

1148
01:08:27,306 --> 01:08:28,155
Alright, everyone,

1149
01:08:28,180 --> 01:08:29,740
thank you for all your hard work.

1150
01:08:29,759 --> 01:08:32,398
Thank you very much.

